                <i class="fas fa-star"></i>
                <i class="fas fa-star-half-alt"></i>
                <i class="far fa-star"></i>
                <span>4.63(56)</span>
                <p><i class="fas fa-eye"></i> 345 views</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="receipt-main">
            <div class="receipt-main-image">
                <img src="/images/Salads/shopska-salata.jpg" alt="shopska-salata">
            </div>
            <div class="receipt-main-products">
                <h4>Products:</h4>
                <ol type="1">
                    <li>2 pieces, mature, red tomatoes</li>
                    <li>1 count cucumbers</li>
                    <li>1 head, small onion onion</li>
                    <li>4 - 5 pieces olives</li>
                    <li>150 - 200 g cheese</li>
                    <li>1 tablespoon vinegar</li>
                    <li>1 - 2 tablespoons olive oil</li>
                    <li>1 cup of salt</li>
                </ol>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="receipt-content">
            <h4>Receipt:</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Cut the onion into thin half moons and grind it with a little salt in a large bowl. If desired, you can also use red onions. Cut the tomatoes and cucumbers into pieces and add them to the onion.</li>
                <li>Pour the peppers, peel them and add them to the salad, cut into small rows, then the olives. Stir the salad, add, pour the vinegar and olive oil.</li>
                <li>Crumble the cheese on the vegetables, sprinkle with chopped parsley, garnish with an olive in the middle and serve.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </article>
